ce:section.ce:para:
PAEs have been widely used as food additives, plastic toys of children and other industrial products in our daily life. The water samples in different area were extracted by the prepared carbon dots-based fiber to evaluate the applicability of the fiber in real water samples. Water samples were collected from Yangtze River in Wuhu section and industrial area in Wuhu city. The results for the quantitative determination of the five PAEs in water samples have been presented in Table 5. As shown, in both water samples, no BBP and DMP can be detected when DNOP was below LOQ. But 5.32 μg·L−1 of DEP, 2.09 μg·L−1 of DBP in Yangtze River water sample and 2.34 μg·L−1of DEP, 1.94 μg·L−1 of DBP in industrial area water sample were found. The water samples were spiked at two concentration levels (5 and 10 μg·L−1). The recoveries of five PAEs in both Yangtze River and industrial area water samples are in the range from 84 to 111% at 5 μg·L−1spiked level and 82 to 119% at 10 μgL−1 spiked level, respectively. The RSDs of them ranged between 4.0% and 9.8% (5 μg·L−1 spiked level, three replicates) as well as 4.9–14.7%, (10 μg·L−1 spiked level, three replicates), respectively. The chromatograms of unspiked and spiked Yangtze River water samples were shown in Fig. 5
                        . The locations where the values of five peaks exactly emerge noticeable change by being unspiked and spiked with 5 or 10 μg·L−1 PAEs correspondto the five target analytes in the chromatogram. The specific classification of the target analyte should be based on the retention time on the standard material certificate (Table 6.
                        ).
